♪ Yeah, the guy said, Honey ♪

07:10.680 --> 07:17.728
♪ You're a funny girl ♪

07:17.813 --> 07:19.271
♪ That's me ♪

07:19.356 --> 07:22.024
♪ I just keep them ♪

07:22.109 --> 07:25.361
♪ In stitches ♪

07:27.239 --> 07:30.658
♪ Double in half♪

07:32.619 --> 07:39.625
♪ And though I may be
all wrong for the guy ♪

07:39.709 --> 07:42.837
♪ I'm good for a laugh ♪
[Laughs]

07:42.921 --> 07:44.880
♪ I guess it's not ♪

07:44.965 --> 07:49.385
♪ Funny ♪

07:49.469 --> 07:52.429
♪ Life is far from sunny ♪

07:52.556 --> 07:55.641
[Whispers]
Where are you going?
Get back here.

07:55.725 --> 08:01.897
♪ When the laugh is over ♪

08:01.982 --> 08:08.654
♪ And the joke's on you ♪

08:08.738 --> 08:10.322
♪ A girl ♪

08:10.407 --> 08:15.035
♪ Oughta have a sense
of humor ♪

08:15.120 --> 08:18.414
♪ That's one thing ♪

08:18.498 --> 08:21.667
♪ You really need for sure ♪

08:21.751 --> 08:24.962
♪ When you're a ♪

08:25.046 --> 08:28.465
♪ Funny ♪

08:28.550 --> 08:31.260
♪ Girl ♪

08:31.344 --> 08:36.891
♪ The fella said
a funny ♪

08:36.975 --> 08:39.685
♪ Girl ♪

08:41.062 --> 08:42.938
Funny...

08:43.023 --> 08:46.025
♪ How it ain't ♪

08:46.109 --> 08:48.360
♪ So ♪

08:48.445 --> 08:50.988
♪ Funny ♪

08:53.200 --> 09:00.456
♪ Funny girl ♪♪

09:05.253 --> 09:07.254
Ms. Corcoran?

09:13.762 --> 09:15.888
I'm Rachel Berry.

09:17.140 --> 09:19.141
I'm your daughter.

09:26.191 --> 09:28.484
Did you ever regret it?

09:29.819 --> 09:31.403
Yes.

09:31.488 --> 09:33.405
Then no.

09:33.490 --> 09:35.658
Then so much.

09:35.742 --> 09:40.120
But when did you realize
it was the right time
for me to find you?

09:40.205 --> 09:43.082
[Chuckles]
I saw you sing
at sectionals.

09:43.166 --> 09:44.750
You were
extraordinary.

09:44.834 --> 09:46.835
You were me.
[Laughs]

09:49.047 --> 09:54.301
Was it hard for you
to not become a star, to not
have your dreams come true?

09:55.845 --> 09:58.931
It felt like
a broken promise.

09:59.015 --> 10:03.102
Like the fisher king's wound-
it never heals.

10:03.186 --> 10:06.313
Wow. Genetics
really are amazing.

10:06.398 --> 10:10.109
You see the world
with the same fierce
theatricality as I do.

10:10.193 --> 10:12.569
Even the way we're sitting
right now is so dramatic,

10:12.654 --> 10:14.571
and yet we feel
so comfortable with it.

10:14.656 --> 10:17.366
I've missed so much.

10:23.331 --> 10:26.750
How do you feel?
Thirsty.

10:28.795 --> 10:31.714
When I was little
and I used to get sad,

10:31.798 --> 10:34.383
my dads would bring me
a glass of water.

10:36.052 --> 10:41.223
It got so I couldn't tell
if I was sad or just thirsty.

10:48.398 --> 10:50.607
Uh...

10:50.692 --> 10:52.735
I shouldn't have done this.

10:56.865 --> 10:59.241
This was supposed to feel good.

10:59.326 --> 11:04.747
W-We were supposed to have
some kind of slow-motion...
run into each other's arms.

11:04.831 --> 11:07.666
- This is all wrong.
- Maybe we can just
g-go to dinner or something?

11:07.751 --> 11:09.752
Just to get over
the initial shock.

11:15.008 --> 11:17.426
I'm so sorry, Rachel.

11:19.304 --> 11:21.013
Uh-

11:21.097 --> 11:23.849
I'll- I'll call you.

11:36.237 --> 11:39.948
Oh, hey, Finn. Come on in.
I'm learning all this
amazing stuff about Lady Gaga.

11:40.033 --> 11:42.701
She's got this thing
called the Haus of Gaga,

11:42.786 --> 11:47.456
this collective of artists
and designers who collaborate on
her styles, stage sets, music.

11:47.540 --> 11:51.293
I think it's an exciting model
for what we could be doing in Glee Club.

11:51.378 --> 11:55.464
Yeah, that's kinda what
I wanted to talk to you about.
I don't wanna do Lady Gaga.

11:55.548 --> 11:58.092
And I suspect that,
with the exception of Kurt,

11:58.176 --> 12:01.678
that none of the other guys
are gonna want to do it either.

12:01.763 --> 12:05.099
I just feel like
we're always doing whatever
the girls want us to do.

12:05.183 --> 12:08.268
Yeah.
Yeah, you're right.

12:08.353 --> 12:12.147
You know, maybe I haven't
been listening to you guys
hard enough.

12:14.025 --> 12:16.693
So let's find a solution.

12:16.778 --> 12:20.447
Well, I, uh—
I actually already have one.

12:20.573 --> 12:23.951
[School Bell Rings]
You're wrong. It's a good name.
It's a rock star name.

12:24.035 --> 12:27.246
You want to name our daughter
Jack Daniels? She's a girl!

12:27.330 --> 12:29.164
Okay, fine, whatever.
Jackie Daniels.

12:29.249 --> 12:30.958
The name is not the point!

12:31.042 --> 12:34.503
I told you this.
I'm giving up the baby so I
don't have to do this with you.

12:34.587 --> 12:36.505
This is good for you.

12:36.589 --> 12:39.967
Now you can go off
and be a rock star yourself.

12:42.345 --> 12:43.929
I love wearing
champagne bubbles.

12:44.013 --> 12:46.265
I get to express
a whole different side
of myself.

12:46.349 --> 12:50.144
Even though I'm painfully shy
and obsessed with death,
I'm a really effervescent person.

12:52.063 --> 12:55.315
- Excuse me! Were you
dropped on your heads?
- What was that?

12:55.400 --> 12:57.609
I think you heard me.

12:57.694 --> 13:00.028
I'm just saying,
pick on me, that's fine.

13:00.113 --> 13:03.699
- But don't throw around a girl.
- Lately we haven't been able
to tell the difference.

13:03.783 --> 13:05.993
We're not gaga
for Gaga.

13:06.077 --> 13:07.995
You dress
all freaky,

13:08.079 --> 13:10.164
and then you rub it
in everybody's faces.

13:10.248 --> 13:13.041
I don't wanna
look at it all day.
It's weird.

13:13.126 --> 13:14.585
Makes my eyes tired.

13:14.669 --> 13:17.504
You wanna switch it up a bit,
just go from Gap
to Banana Republic.

13:17.589 --> 13:20.507
It's called being theatrical.
We're showing off who we are.

13:20.592 --> 13:23.760
It's the same thing you do
when you go to school
with your football uniforms on.

13:23.845 --> 13:25.971
You're expressing yourself,
and we have every right
to do the same.

13:26.055 --> 13:29.183
Well, the next time
you wanna express yourself
and look like a circus freak,

13:29.267 --> 13:33.479
don't be shocked when my fist
feels like expressing itself
against your chin!

13:33.563 --> 13:37.524
Okay? I'll knock
that crazy-fool crepe-paper
nonsense off you.

13:37.609 --> 13:41.945
- Let's go.
- You don't wanna be late for
your appointment at Supercuts!

13:42.030 --> 13:43.947
Watch your mouth,
Hummel!

13:44.032 --> 13:45.949
And you know what,
fancy?

13:46.034 --> 13:47.910
You don't need
an appointment
at Supercuts.

13:48.036 --> 13:50.579
They love walk-ins.
[Both Chuckling]

13:52.624 --> 13:56.126
- [School Bell Rings]
- Little monsters, take a bow.

13:56.211 --> 13:58.670
[Will Laughing]
All right!

13:58.755 --> 14:01.006
Ladies, Kurt,
I am really, really impressed.

14:01.090 --> 14:03.884
[Will] Siéntate.
You know what the best part is?

14:03.968 --> 14:07.513
Each one of your costumes
shows off a different aspect
of your personalities.

14:07.597 --> 14:09.014
Wait,
where's Rachel?

14:09.098 --> 14:11.016
I only notice because
five minutes have gone by...

14:11.100 --> 14:13.018
without her saying
something totally obnoxious.

14:13.102 --> 14:16.021
Rachel kinda got
some intense news
yesterday.

14:16.105 --> 14:18.357
We were spying
on Vocal Adrenaline and-

14:18.441 --> 14:22.152
Guys, that's not fair!
You gotta stop doing that.

14:22.237 --> 14:24.905
But, uh, you know, wh-
what'd you find out?

14:24.989 --> 14:26.573
Okay, y'all ready?

14:26.658 --> 14:30.619
Ms. Corcoran, their coach,
she's Rachel's mom.

14:30.703 --> 14:32.663
Are you serious?

14:32.747 --> 14:35.791
- Way to bury the lead, Mercedes.
- We're screwed.

14:35.875 --> 14:38.168
Rachel's gonna jump ship
over to Vocal Adrenaline.

14:38.253 --> 14:41.630
Never. I really don't want
to talk about it though.
I'm still processing the news.

14:41.714 --> 14:45.133
And my dads are moving
my therapist to our spare room
later this afternoon.

14:45.218 --> 14:48.303
A-A-All I know is that
I'm not going anywhere...

14:48.388 --> 14:52.599
and I've chosen a Lady Gaga look
that expresses the longing for
a childhood I was deprived of.

14:52.684 --> 14:54.977
You look terrible.
I look awesome.

14:55.061 --> 14:58.021
I think it's
the Kermit the Frog look.

14:58.106 --> 14:59.731
And we have a jumper.

14:59.816 --> 15:01.400
[Sighs]

15:01.484 --> 15:04.361
Well, my dads can't sew,
so these are just stapled on.

15:04.445 --> 15:07.364
Why don't we worry
about this later and try
to focus on the song.

15:07.448 --> 15:08.991
Couldn't agree more.
Hit it.

15:09.075 --> 15:11.285
♪ Rah-rah, ah-ah-ah ♪

15:11.369 --> 15:13.328
♪ Roma-Roma-ma ♪

15:13.413 --> 15:15.372
♪ Gaga, ooh-la-la ♪

15:15.456 --> 15:17.416
♪ Want your bad romance ♪

15:17.500 --> 15:21.670
♪ I want your ugly
I want your disease ♪

15:21.754 --> 15:24.381
♪ I want your everything
as long as it's free ♪

15:24.465 --> 15:27.384
